 Mtns.  Brother Zephyl didn't spawn after 5+ hours straight of killing placeholders.  The 'A drake' spawned quite a lot, think we killed it least 10-15 times.  Killed Maldyl twice.  Others in zone killed the drake a couple of times &amp; I think Maldyl once.  Never saw HAsten either.  Had my little Druid tracking (same account, I can't 2-box it), the aforementioned Drid &amp; Ranger tracking until they had to log, then another Ranger helping later on.<br><br>I logged in today, and not only was Zephyl up but so was Mortimer Syytrak (go figure, but no he didn't drop the vest).  So I got that done in about half an hour 45 minutes.  Kind of bad when the turn-in NPC takes as long to camp as one of the hunted NPCs.<br><br>Went to PoK, bought the Gather Shadows Scroll, &amp; made the Shadow Silk (yes it's the scroll, shadow wolf pelt, and a silk swatch, and trivials around 50-51...mine's 46 &amp; got it first time).  Then combined everything for the robe.<br><br>For Raster I didn't use any kind of special method or anything.  Once the room was cleared I just sat in the corner behind the PH spawn spot &amp; killed the PH, then the other 4-5 spawns that pop in &amp; wander into that room in the 10 minutes or so after the PH.  Then I sat there bored for 15 minutes.  Rinse &amp; repeat.</p>&nbsp;<br>Harik Sarome<br>The Wandering Monk of Xegony<br>Soldiers of Fortune</td></tr>
